Scope of the Reference Implementation

This reference implementation includes the runtime engine, canonical demo, scripts, outputs, reference outputs, validation traces, and supporting artifacts provided in this release.

STOCRS defines a deterministic structural computation model in which correctness emerges from dependency resolution rather than execution order or time.

The reference implementation establishes the following conceptual model:

resolve(nodes) ->
    evaluate nodes whose dependencies are satisfied
    repeat until no further resolution is possible

Final correctness emerges when:

structural_closure = all dependencies satisfied

The reference implementation demonstrates:

• computation from incomplete and fragmented states
• independence from execution order and timing
• bounded information sharing between systems
• deterministic convergence across independent systems
• structural closure leading to identical final results
• replay-verifiable deterministic outcomes
• correctness under conflict through abstention and structural resolution

The reference implementation is provided to demonstrate the feasibility of structure-based computation without reliance on time, sequence, or synchronization.

Conformance

An implementation is considered compatible with the STOCRS reference architecture if it preserves the core structural principles demonstrated by the implementation, including:

• correctness derived from structural dependency resolution
• independence from execution order
• independence from global time or synchronization
• deterministic convergence across systems
• reproducibility under replay conditions

Independent implementations are permitted and encouraged.

