Closing Statement

STOCRS is published to explore the possibility that computation correctness can emerge from structure rather than time, sequence, or synchronization.

The project is released openly to encourage independent research, validation, and implementation of structure-based computation models.

Computation, long governed by order and timing, may also be understood as a process of structural resolution.

STOCRS is offered as a reference architecture for that exploration.
